Another alternative is to extract your executorService as a field so that shutdown or shutdownNow is always invoked even if the test has a failure:
private ExecutorService executorService;

@Before
public void setUp() {
  executorService = Executors.newCachedThreadPool();
}

@After
public void tearDown() {
  executorService.shutdownNow();
}

